---
const pageTitle = "About Astro";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<title>{pageTitle}</title>
		<style>
			* {
				margin: 0;
				padding: 0;
				box-sizing: border-box;
			}

			body {
				font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
				line-height: 1.6;
				color: #333;
				background: #f5f5f5;
			}

			.container {
				max-width: 800px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 2rem;
			}

			header {
				text-align: center;
				padding: 3rem 0;
			}

			h1 {
				font-size: 2.5rem;
				color: #222;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			h2 {
				font-size: 1.75rem;
				color: #333;
				margin-top: 2rem;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			p {
				font-size: 1.125rem;
				color: #666;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			main {
				background: white;
				border-radius: 8px;
				padding: 2rem;
				box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
			}

			.subtitle {
				font-size: 1.25rem;
				color: #888;
			}

			ul {
				margin: 1rem 0 1rem 2rem;
			}

			li {
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
				color: #666;
			}

			.nav {
				margin-top: 2rem;
				padding-top: 2rem;
				border-top: 1px solid #eee;
			}

			a {
				color: #0066cc;
				text-decoration: none;
			}

			a:hover {
				text-decoration: underline;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="container">
			<header>
				<h1>{pageTitle}</h1>
				<p class="subtitle">The web framework for content-driven websites</p>
			</header>
			<main>
				<p>
					Astro is a modern web framework designed for building fast, content-focused websites.
					It allows developers to build websites that ship less JavaScript to the browser,
					resulting in faster load times and better performance.
				</p>

				<h2>Key Features</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Component Islands:</strong> Astro pioneered the islands architecture, allowing you to build interactive UI components while keeping the rest of your page static.</li>
					<li><strong>Zero JS by Default:</strong> Astro generates HTML with zero client-side JavaScript by default, adding interactivity only where needed.</li>
					<li><strong>UI Agnostic:</strong> Use your favorite UI framework like React, Vue, Svelte, or others. You can even mix multiple frameworks in the same project.</li>
					<li><strong>Fast Performance:</strong> Automatic optimization means your site loads quickly with minimal JavaScript overhead.</li>
					<li><strong>Easy to Learn:</strong> Astro's component syntax is similar to HTML, making it accessible for developers of all skill levels.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Perfect For</h2>
				<p>
					Astro excels at building content-driven websites like blogs, marketing sites,
					documentation, portfolios, and e-commerce stores. If your site is focused on
					delivering content to users quickly, Astro is an excellent choice.
				</p>

				<div class="nav">
					<a href="/">‚Üê Back to Home</a>
				</div>
			</main>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
